## ‚ú® Key Features

- **Production API** ‚Äî FastAPI backend with auth, chat APIs, and OpenAI-compatible endpoints ‚Üí [Server setup](https://naumanhsa.github.io/neurosurfer/server/)

- **Intelligent Agents** ‚Äî Build ReAct, SQL, and RAG agents with minimal code, optimized for specific tasks ‚Üí [Learn about agents](https://naumanhsa.github.io/neurosurfer/api-reference/agents/)

- **Rich Tool Ecosystem** ‚Äî Built-in tools (calculator, web calls, files) plus easy custom tools ‚Üí [Explore tools](https://naumanhsa.github.io/neurosurfer/api-reference/tools/)

- **RAG System** ‚Äî Ingest, chunk, and retrieve relevant context for your LLMs ‚Üí [RAG System](https://naumanhsa.github.io/neurosurfer/api-reference/rag/)

- **Vector Databases** ‚Äî Built-in ChromaDB with an extensible interface for other stores ‚Üí [Vector stores](https://naumanhsa.github.io/neurosurfer/api-reference/vectorstores/)

- **Multi-LLM Support** ‚Äî OpenAI, Transformers/Unsloth, vLLM, Llama.cpp, and OpenAI-compatible APIs ‚Üí [Model docs](https://naumanhsa.github.io/neurosurfer/api-reference/models/)

## üì¶ Install Options

**pip (recommended)**
```bash
pip install -U neurosurfer
```

**pip + full LLM stack**
```bash
pip install -U "neurosurfer[torch]"
```

**From source**
```bash
git clone https://github.com/NaumanHSA/neurosurfer.git
cd neurosurfer && pip install -e ".[torch]"
```

CUDA notes (Linux x86_64):
```bash
# Wheels bundle CUDA; you just need a compatible NVIDIA driver.
pip install -U torch --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu124
# or CPU-only:
pip install -U torch --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cpu
```

